derivation.yuyuan_name: late 16th cent.: from medieval Latin predominat- 'predominated', from the verb predominari (see pre-, dominate)

entry.def: If one type of person or thing predominates in a group, there is more of that type of person or thing in the group than of any other.

example.ex: In older age groups women predominate because men tend to die younger...
example.tran: 在老年群体中女性占大多数，因为男性的寿命往往较短。

example.ex: All nationalities were represented — but the English predominated.
example.tran: 所有国家都有代表出席——但是英格兰人占大多数。

entry.tran: 占主导地位；占支配地位；突出
entry.def: When a feature or quality predominates, it is the most important or noticeable one in a situation.

example.ex: He wants to create a society where Islamic principles predominate.
example.tran: 他想创造一个以伊斯兰教戒律为主导的社会。

means.word_mean: 1. be larger in number, quantity, power, status or importance;
2. appear very large or occupy a commanding position;
